C%221565%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vazquez%20and%20Xavi%20smile%20at%20the%20camera%20for%20a%20selfie%20as%20Vazquez%20points%20to%20her%20ring%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664f6f93a961b37edf3949f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221037%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVazquez%20and%20Xavi%20got%20engaged%20with%20a%20%2469%20Etsy%20ring.%3Cp%3EViviana%20Vazquez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EViviana%20Vazquez%20and%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20Xavi%20plan%20to%20get%20married%20in%20August%202025%20with%20a%20wedding%20budget%20of%20%2420K.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20are%20very%20open%20about%20finances%20and%20are%20very%20mindful%20of%20each%20other's%20financial%20situations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20feels%20like%20a%20huge%20milestone%20for%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20save%20and%20pay%20for%20their%20wedding%20themselves.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20love%20story%20started%20on%20the%20soccer%20field%20when%20we%20were%20both%20students%20at%20Baruch%20College.%20Xavi%20was%20the%20starting%20goalie%2C%20and%20I%20was%20the%20team%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20dating%20in%20October%202016%2C%20got%20engaged%20on%20October%209%2C%202021%2C%20and%20will%20marry%20on%20August%2030%2C%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Faverage-american-debt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20into%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20wedding%20you%20can't%20afford%20is%20the%20worst%20way%20to%20start%20a%20marriage.%20That's%20why%20we're%20having%20a%20long%20engagement%3A%20to%20make%20planning%20and%20saving%20for%20our%20wedding%20stress-free%20while%20balancing%20other%20financial%20responsibilities%20and%20still%20being%20able%20to%20prioritize%20health%2C%20travel%2C%20and%20leisure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d268701-51d0-4580-b96e-e86f07ffdb85%5C%22%3EWe've%20had%20difficult%20conversations%20about%20finances%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EXavi%20and%20I%20are%20very%20open%20about%20finances%20nowadays%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20always%20this%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXavi%20and%20I%20were%20both%20the%20first%20in%20our%20families%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-succeed-in-school-first-generation-college-student-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduate%20from%20college%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20didn't%20know%20what%20we%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%20but%20just%20studied%20hard%2C%20got%20good%20grades%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20make%20our%20parents%20proud.%20We%20both%20became%20teachers%20in%20New%20York%20City%20public%20schools%20because%20teaching%20would%20give%20us%20stability%20and%20plenty%20of%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Viviana%20Vazquez%20wears%20a%20graduation%20gown%20as%20she%20sits%20with%20her%20fianc%C3%A9%20Xavi%20on%20a%20bench%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664f6f46a961b37edf394957%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVazquez%20graduated%20from%20Baruch%20College%20in%202018.%3Cp%3EViviana%20Vazquez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20come%20from%20generational%20poverty%2C%20and%20when%20I%20told%20my%20parents%2C%20who%20are%20immigrants%20from%20Mexico%2C%20about%20my%20starting%20salary%20of%20%2457%2C000%2C%20they%20thought%20I%20was%20financially%20set%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20they%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Brich.%26quot%3B%20I%20became%20my%20family's%20breadwinner%2C%20paying%20for%20our%20groceries%2C%20utility%20bills%2C%20and%20half%20the%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%2022%2C%20I%20was%20financially%20clueless%20and%20had%20accumulated%20over%20%2415%2C000%20in%20student%20loans%20and%20credit%20card%20debt.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Xavi%20was%20debt-free%2C%20saving%20a%20ton%2C%20and%20maxing%20out%20his%20403(b)%20employee%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EXavi%20didn't%20know%20how%20much%20I%20was%20struggling%20until%202019%20when%20he%20brought%20up%20moving%20in%20together%2C%20and%20I%20started%20crying%20mid-dinner.%20Despite%20being%20together%20for%20over%20two%20years%2C%20I%20had%20never%20brought%20up%20my%20financial%20situation%20%E2%80%94%20or%20my%20family's%20%E2%80%94%20because%20I%20was%20embarrassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20sure%20Xavi%20would%20break%20up%20with%20me%20after%20that%20conversation%2C%20but%20I%20was%20so%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20talked%20for%20hours%20about%20finances%2C%20and%20he%20suggested%20helping%20me%20in%20little%20ways%2C%20like%20paying%20for%20all%20of%20our%20dates%20and%20not%20going%20out%20so%20much%20so%20I%20could%20focus%20on%20paying%20off%20my%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec01da75-3746-4f01-9843-be179d6eca50%5C%22%3EWe%20got%20engaged%20with%20a%20%2457%20Etsy%20ring%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202021%2C%20I%20had%20transitioned%20out%20of%20my%20teaching%20job%20and%20into%20a%20role%20at%20a%20fintech%20startup%20in%20Atlanta.%20Xavi%20also%20decided%20to%20quit%20teaching%2C%20moved%20to%20Atlanta%20with%20me%2C%20and%20started%20a%20three-month%20software%20engineering%20boot%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20we%20were%20living%20off%20of%20my%20fintech%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20also%20%2457%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20savings.%20We%20had%20also%20been%20talking%20about%20an%20engagement%2C%20but%20because%20times%20were%20tough%2C%20we%20bought%20a%20%2457%20ring%20on%20Etsy%20to%20formalize%20our%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%209%2C%202021%2C%20Xavi%20took%20me%20back%20to%20the%20place%20where%20we%20first%20said%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you%26quot%3B%20to%20each%20other%20in%202017%3A%20a%20gondola%20ride%20in%20New%20Orleans.%20We%20watched%20the%20sunset%2C%20and%20Xavi%20proposed%20with%20a%20hand-written%20love%20letter%20I%20%26quot%3Bfound%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20lagoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Viviana%20Vazquez%20and%20Xavi%20kiss%20aboard%20a%20gondola%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665755ee1cd3b17790412abb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVazquez%20and%20Xavi%20got%20engaged%20at%20the%20same%20place%20they%20first%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ERobert%20Dula%2FNola%20Gondola%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20knew%20it%20would%20take%20a%20while%20to%20become%20financially%20stable%20again%2C%20so%20we%20agreed%20on%20a%20long%20engagement%20so%20that%20we%20could%20save%20up.%20We%20knew%20from%20the%20start%20that%20we'd%20be%20paying%20for%20the%20wedding%20ourselves%20and%20wanted%20to%20do%20so%20without%20taking%20on%20debt%20or%20adding%20any%20extra%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20we%20both%20landed%20six-figure%20tech%20jobs%20and%20moved%20back%20to%20New%20York%20City.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20we%20were%20back%20on%20our%20feet%20and%20finally%20felt%20financially%20comfortable%20enough%20to%20start%20saving%20for%20our%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221fae9322-bb6e-43d9-860e-b9c433dc2641%5C%22%3EOur%20wedding%20budget%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20wedding%20budget%20of%20%2420%2C000%2C%20with%20a%20guest%20list%20of%20around%20120%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20chose%20a%20destination%20wedding%20at%20a%20resort%20in%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C%20Mexico%2C%20because%20we%20want%20to%20share%20beautiful%20travel%20memories%20with%20our%20loved%20ones%2C%20especially%20since%20many%20of%20my%20family%20members%20have%20never%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20travel%20or%20stay%20in%20an%20all-inclusive%20resort%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20the%20budget%20work%2C%20we%20agreed%20not%20to%20have%20wedding%20parties%20or%20lavish%20bachelor%20and%20bachelorette%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20breakdown%20of%20our%20%2420%2C000%20budget%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2410%2C000%20for%20the%20resort%20ceremony%20and%20reception%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20which%20includes%20a%20wedding%20planner%2C%20photography%2C%20catering%2C%20entertainment%2C%20and%20a%20free%20stay%20for%20the%20couple.%20We%20plan%20to%20keep%20the%20decor%20as%20simple%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%241%2C000%20for%20the%20rings%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20We%20plan%20on%20getting%20simple%20gold-plated%20rings%20because%20we're%20not%20big%20on%20flashy%20jewelry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%242%2C000%20for%20our%20wedding%20attire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20including%20my%20dress%2C%20Xavi's%20tux%2C%20and%20our%20shoes%20and%20accessories.%20While%20I'm%20excited%20to%20try%20on%20wedding%20dresses%2C%20I'm%20not%20willing%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20%241%2C000%20on%20a%20dress%20I'll%20only%20wear%20once.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2450%20for%20the%20marriage%20license%20from%20City%20Hall%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%24800%20for%20a%20family%20dinner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20after%20our%20civil%20wedding.%20Some%20of%20my%20family%20members%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20travel%20to%20Mexico%2C%20so%20we%20plan%20to%20invite%20them%20to%20dinner%20after%20our%20City%20Hall%20civil%20wedding.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%245%2C000%20for%20financial%20assistance%20for%20my%20family.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20all%20of%20our%20loved%20ones%20can%20afford%20to%20travel%20and%20stay%20in%20the%20resort%20with%20us.%20We%20plan%20to%20help%20subsidize%20five%20rooms%20for%2010%20family%20members%20by%20contributing%20%241%2C000%20per%20room%2C%20or%20half%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%241%2C150%20for%20miscellaneous%20expenses.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EXavi%20and%20I%20each%20plan%20on%20saving%20%2410%2C000.%20We%20put%20at%20least%20%24500%20a%20month%20into%20our%20respective%20high-yield%20savings%20accounts%2C%20which%20earn%204.6%25%20to%205.5%25%20interest%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20opened%20a%200%25%20introductory%20APR%20credit%20card%20to%20cover%20our%20wedding%20expenses.%20This%20way%2C%20we%20can%20strategically%20allow%20our%20wedding%20funds%20to%20grow%20at%20a%20much%20higher%20rate%20before%20using%20them%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20Xavi%20has%20been%20able%20to%20save%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20than%20me%20since%20he%20doesn't%20have%20as%20many%20familial%20financial%20responsibilities%20as%20I%20do%2C%20and%20we're%20OK%20with%20that.%20We're%20very%20conscious%20of%20proportionate%20budgeting%20and%20being%20mindful%20of%20each%20other's%20financial%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22887b2c27-5af7-4ce9-8f1b-bf393dca8de4%5C%22%3EIt%20feels%20like%20a%20huge%20milestone%20to%20save%20and%20pay%20for%20our%20own%20wedding%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20Xavi%20upgraded%20my%20Etsy%20engagement%20ring%20to%20a%201.7-carat%20lab%20diamond%20ring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vazquez%20has%20sparkly%20pink%20nails%20as%20she%20wears%20her%20diamond%20engagement%20ring%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664f7016a961b37edf394ae5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%201.7-carat%20diamond%20engagement%20ring.%3Cp%3EViviana%20Vazquez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20first-generation%20college%20grads%2C%20we%20never%20thought%20we'd%20earn%20as%20much%20as%20we%20do%20today.%20In%20my%20current%20job%2C%20my%20total%20compensation%20is%20around%20%24180%2C000%2C%20while%20Xavi's%20is%20around%20%24140%2C000%20a%20year.%20Getting%20here%20has%20come%20with%20challenges%2C%20like%20navigating%20guilt%20and%20imposter%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20me%2C%20%2420%2C000%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20so%20it%20feels%20like%20a%20huge%20milestone%20to%20be%20able%20to%20save%20it%20an