e%20inside%20the%20home.%20The%20roof%20meanwhile%20is%20topped%20with%20an%20ornately%20carved%20French%20pediment.%20The%20palatial%20quarters%20boast%20five%20halls%3A%20Reception%20Hall%2C%20Painting%20Room%2C%20Sculpture%20Room%2C%20Billiards%20Room%20and%20%3Cem%3EThakur%20Dalan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(place%20of%20worship).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20rooms%20bears%20the%20nostalgia%20of%20the%20art%20that%20Rajendra%20collected%20along%20his%20travels.%20He%20loved%20dabbling%20in%20it%3B%20the%20Bohemian%20goblets%2C%20French%20Ormulo%20clocks%2C%20swords%20from%20Toledo%2C%20and%20Venetian%20mirrors%20are%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F146531%2Fnews-world-ethnic-day-15-must-have-ethnic-souvenirs-from-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esouvenirs%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren%E2%80%99t%20delighting%20your%20senses%2C%20huge%20oil%20paintings%20will.%20These%20include%20Rubens%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98The%20Marriage%20of%20St%20Catherine%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Infant%20Hercules%20Strangling%20the%20Serpent%E2%80%99%20by%20Joshua%20Reynolds%2C%20paintings%20by%20Raja%20Ravi%20Varma%2C%20Jan%20Van%20Goyen%2C%20and%20Giovanni%20Battista%2C%20and%20sculptures%20of%20Venus%2C%20Apollo%2C%20Homer%2C%20and%20other%20mythical%20and%20real%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20the%20palace%20houses%2076%20rare%20artworks%20brought%20from%20Italy%20and%20Belgium%20in%201830%2C%20and%20a%20two-cornered%20biocome%20that%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20worn%20by%20Napoleon%20Bonaparte%20during%20his%20military%20campaigns.%20The%20originality%20is%20still%20debated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYour%20way%20will%20be%20illuminated%20by%20the%20light%20bouncing%20off%20the%2019th-century%20disco%20balls.%20The%20palace%20is%20a%20balance%20between%20grandeur%20and%20a%20warm%20place%20called%20%E2%80%98home%E2%80%99.%20But%20while%20it%20is%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20touch%20for%20artefacts%20that%20draws%20visitors%20to%20the%20place%2C%20it%20was%20once%20the%20zoo%20that%20made%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20Marble%20Palace%20is%20a%20palatial%20nineteenth-century%20mansion%20in%20North%20Kolkata%20at%2046%2C%20Muktaram%20Babu%20Street.%20It%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best-preserved%20mansions%20of%20nineteenth-century%20Calcutta.%20The%20mansion%20is%20famous%20for%20its%20marble%20walls%2C%20floors%2C%20and%20sculptures%2C%20from%20which%20it%20derives%20its%20name.%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FM7cvGln1tn%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FM7cvGln1tn%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rupak%20Chattopadhyay%20(%40RupakChatto)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRupakChatto%2Fstatus%2F1712823180560080902%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2013%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EMagpies%20and%20golden%20pheasants%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EHirendra%20Mullick%20%E2%80%94%20resident%20and%20curator%20of%20Marble%20Palace%20%E2%80%94%20credited%20Mullick%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dbotanist%2Bthe%2Bbetter%2Bindia%26rlz%3D1C1YTUH_enIN1048IN1048%26oq%3Dbotanist%2Bthe%2Bbetter%2Bindia%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIHCAEQIRigATIHCAIQIRigAdIBCDQzNzFqMGo0qAIAsAIA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebackground%20in%20botany%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ornithology%20for%20creating%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20privately-owned%20zoo.%20Called%20Nilmani%20Niketan%20after%20Rajendra%20Mullick%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20the%20zoo%20was%20an%20attempt%20to%20preserve%20and%20display%20herbivores%2C%20owing%20to%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20vegetarian%20diet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERare%20birds%20like%20albino%20peacocks%2C%20hyacinthine%20macaw%2C%20bird%20of%20Alexandria%2C%20trucan%2C%20hawk-headed%20parakeets%2C%20silver%20and%20golden%20pheasants%2C%20magpies%2C%20hornbills%2C%20and%20mute%20swans%3B%20long-tailed%20monkeys%2C%20spotted%20deer%2C%20barking%20deer%2C%20red-butt%20baboon%2C%20and%20porcupines%20thrived%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Hirendra%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CEverything%20is%20preserved%20to%20protect%20the%20glamour%20and%20glory%20of%20the%20tradition%2C%20history%20and%20ambience%20of%20the%20past.%20Everything%20is%20religiously%20followed%20as%20instructed%20by%20the%20founder.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20sunlight%20bathes%20the%20sweeping%20lawns%20in%20a%20yellow%20glow%2C%20the%20glint%20bounces%20off%20the%20marble%20marvel%20%E2%80%94%20a%20symbol%20of%20Kolkata%E2%80%99s%20still-standing%20royalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fculture%2Fheritage%2Fthe-past-preserved-in-a-marble-palace%2Fcid%2F1673318%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20past%20preserved%20in%20a%20Marble%20Palace%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Saurajit%20Mazumdar%2C%20Published%20on%2031%20October%202018.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cntraveller.in%2Fstory%2Fmarble-palace-kolkata-the-story-behind-kolkatas-mansion-of-curiosities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarble%20Palace%2C%20Kolkata%3A%20the%20story%20behind%20Kolkata%E2%80%99s%20mansion%20of%20curiosities%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Conde%20Nast%20Traveller%2C%20Published%20on%208%20February%202022.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5